To get PDF builtin fonts execute in this directory.

All bundled Noto fonts are gzip-compressed TTF files from notofonts/noto-fonts
(SIL OFL):

	https://github.com/notofonts/noto-fonts

Text families:

	base=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/notofonts/noto-fonts/main/hinted/ttf
	for f in \
	  NotoSerif/NotoSerif-Regular.ttf \
	  NotoSerif/NotoSerif-Bold.ttf \
	  NotoSerif/NotoSerif-Italic.ttf \
	  NotoSerif/NotoSerif-BoldItalic.ttf \
	  NotoSans/NotoSans-Regular.ttf \
	  NotoSans/NotoSans-Bold.ttf \
	  NotoSans/NotoSans-Italic.ttf \
	  NotoSans/NotoSans-BoldItalic.ttf \
	  NotoSansMono/NotoSansMono-Regular.ttf \
	  NotoSansMono/NotoSansMono-Bold.ttf; do \
	    name=$(basename "$f"); \
	    curl -L --fail -o "$name" "$base/$f"; \
	    gzip -9 "$name"; \
	done

Companion fonts for built-in math/symbol coverage:

	base=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/notofonts/noto-fonts/main/hinted/ttf
	for f in \
	  NotoSansMath/NotoSansMath-Regular.ttf \
	  NotoSansSymbols/NotoSansSymbols-Regular.ttf \
	  NotoSansSymbols2/NotoSansSymbols2-Regular.ttf; do \
	    name=$(basename "$f"); \
	    curl -L --fail -o "$name" "$base/$f"; \
	    gzip -9 "$name"; \
	done

Noto Sans Mono has no italic variants in this bundle; Regular is reused for Italic,
and Bold is reused for BoldItalic.
